50|$|In 2008, the AAI {{presented}} a full statement of its position to the Obama administration titled <b>The</b> Next <b>Antitrust</b> Agenda: <b>The</b> American <b>Antitrust</b> Institute’s Transition Report on Competition Policy to the 44th President. In 2013, the AAI celebrated its 15th anniversary, and published {{a history of}} the organization’s first 15 years.|$|R
50|$|In 1914, Congress passed <b>the</b> Clayton <b>Antitrust</b> Act to {{increase}} the government's capacity to intervene and break up big business. The Act removed <b>the</b> application of <b>antitrust</b> laws to trade unions, and introduced controls on the merger of corporations.|$|R
